        "id": "46586993",
        "author": "erbesharat",
        "text": "Root Sustainability | AI / ML Engineer, Senior UX/UI Designer | REMOTE / The Netherlands (or hybrid) | Full-time | Seed-stage + equity\nWe\u2019re Root Sustainability. We help companies understand the environmental footprint of what they produce, starting from messy, incomplete operational data. Think tens of millions of purchase order lines, vague product descriptions, complex supply chains, messy ERP exports, and sustainability logic that does not fit neatly into spreadsheets. Our goal is to turn all of that into auditable, high-granularity insights that feel clear and usable.\nWe\u2019ve recently closed a EUR 1M seed round and are growing the team across both product design and AI. We are building foundational systems, not wrappers, and we are looking for people who want to own real problems end to end.\nRoles:\nAI / ML Engineer\nYou will take the lead on everything AI inside the product. This is a hands-on role: designing, building, evaluating, and deploying LLM-powered features end to end. You will work closely with our engineering team, but you will own the AI direction from prototype to production.\nSenior UX/UI Designer\nYou will own UX/UI end to end: research, flows, wireframes, prototypes, and polished interfaces that make complex sustainability domains feel obvious. You work closely with product and engineering as a partner, shaping what we build next.\nWhat you will do (AI / ML):\nDesign domain-specific inference pipelines for environmental data.\nMake LLM outputs stable, traceable, and reproducible.\nBuild structured reasoning systems, not just chat.\nUse embeddings and semantic similarity to match product descriptions to impact datasets.\nEvaluate models for accuracy, hallucinations, and bias.\nDeploy and operate LLM workloads on AWS.\nIntegrate AI outputs into a Python and Postgres platform.\nWhat you will do (UX/UI):\nLead design for key features: mapping, dashboards, workflows.\nTurn fuzzy sustainability problems into clear, user-centered interfaces.\nBuild prototypes and run lightweight user testing.\nMaintain and evolve a design system in Figma.\nShip frequently with engineers, not just hand off specs.\nYou should apply if (AI / ML):\nYou have 3 to 5+ years experience in software and or ML engineering.\nYou are strong in Python with hands-on LLM or NLP experience.\nYou have deployed AI systems in production on AWS or similar.\nYou think in systems and pipelines, not just prompts.\nYou care about evaluation, monitoring, and reproducibility.\nYou have a product mindset and optimize for clarity and user value.\nYou should apply if (UX/UI):\nYou have around 5+ years experience in UX/UI with a strong portfolio.\nYou are pragmatic: clarity over trends, iteration over perfection.\nYou thrive in early-stage environments with shifting priorities.\nYou know design systems, user research, and can defend decisions.\nBonus: data visualization experience, sustainability interest, accessibility skills.\nConstraints:\nAuthorized to work in the EU or able to work as a contractor.\nAvailability overlaps with 10:00 to 16:00 CET.\nPerks:\nCompetitive salary with stock options.\nRemote-friendly or hybrid with occasional meetups.\nUnlimited vacation days.\nDirect impact on product direction and core systems.\nSmall, kind, motivated team solving hard problems together.\nHow to apply:\nAI / ML Engineer:\nhttps://root-sustainability.homerun.co/ai-ml-engineer\nSenior UX/UI Designer:\nhttps://root-sustainability.homerun.co/senior-ux-ui-designer",
        "created_at": "2026-01-12T11:25:35"
    },
