        "text": "Gatehouse Satcom | Denmark | Lead Software Engineer \u2013 for 5G/ 6G Satellite Communication | ONSITE\nWe\u2019re at the forefront of the 5G satellite revolution, serving a global network of operators. Our technology enables broadband connectivity on mobile devices \u2013 linking devices via satellites in orbit. From concept to commercial operation, we support our customers with feasibility studies, lab kits, and other tools that enable them to validate and verify solutions before deployment.\nYou'll be an integral part of our 5G NTN development team, a blend of seasoned and fresh talents dedicated to advancing 5G NB-IoT/New Radio technologies. Your role will centre on designing, implementing, and testing C/C++ software. Utilizing tools like Git and JIRA, you'll contribute to well-structured and efficiently planned projects.\nFor the right candidate, the role can expand into team lead responsibilities where you will play a key part in planning the day-to-day activities of a self-driven team of 5-10 skilled SW engineers.\nGiven our niche's international scope, occasional travel to meet customers and partners may occur.\nAbout you\nWith an engineering background in software, electronics or embedded systems, your expertise includes:\n- DSP, GPU, ML and Protocol stack development (OSI Layers 1-4) for wireless/communications systems.\n- 5G NB-IoT and New Radio experience and knowledge is an advantage, but strong SW design and development skills, a good system understanding and ability to learn fast is more important.\n- Programming in C, C++ and Python\n- Object-oriented software development expertise is required.\n- Design, Development, testing, and debugging of real-time and embedded software.\n- Optimizing for highly efficient code execution on embedded platforms\n- Experience with development/deployment in Linux as well as Hardware acceleration is an advantage\nYour self-driven nature, teamwork skills, and pioneering spirit are essential for developing new technologies from scratch. Experience in international collaborations and fluency in English will be advantageous.\nApply here:\nhttps://nordictechjobs.com/jobs/xThKxtthRS",
