        "text": "Pickle Robot | Senior Perception Engineers & MLEs | Boston (Charlestown), MA | ONSITE / HYBRID | ROBOTICS\nPickle Robot is solving the long tail of physical automation. We deploy robots that autonomously unload trucks and trailers. The Perception team is expanding to tackle the chaotic reality of the loading dock.\nI am hiring 5 Engineers across 4 technical tracks. I am also looking for short-term (~3-6 months) (computer vision) contractors based around Boston, MA.\nSee below for the opening on my team.\nSenior Robotics Software Engineer: Architect a hybrid C++/Python stack to fuse multi-modal data (RGB-D, LiDAR) into a unified 3D world model\nhttps://jobs.lever.co/picklerobot/adb162fe-056b-4439-ad2e-e7...\nSenior MLE (Eng):\nBuild and deploy robust, high-performance computer vision models for the edge (NVIDIA Orin).\nhttps://jobs.lever.co/picklerobot/adf27300-1af5-4b9e-b471-e6...\nSenior MLE (R&D):\nTame the long tail of rare events and distill massive foundation models/VLMs into lightweight networks.\nhttps://jobs.lever.co/picklerobot/057c340d-4ec0-4f67-907b-8d...\nMLE (Ops/Infra):\nBuild data engines to support active learning and mine interesting events from our fleet data.\nhttps://jobs.lever.co/picklerobot/2dfc1a23-af48-4972-abe6-7d...\nContact: Email noe[at]picklerobot.com and mention \"HN - Who is hiring?\" in the subject. Please specify the role you are applying for and/or whether you are interested in contracting.\nNote: We are also hiring across Engineering in Motion Planning, Task Planning, and Control. View all roles at:\nhttps://jobs.lever.co/picklerobot",
